IRS990.Description: CHILDCARE: THE YWCA CHILDCARE PROGRAMS ARE NATIONALLY ACCREDITED BY THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION FOR THE EDUCATION OF YOUNG CHILDREN AND SERVE CHILDREN FROM THE GREATER NEW BRITAIN AREA. THE PROGRAM IS AVAILABLE FROM 6:30 A.M. - 5:30 P.M., MONDAY THROUGH FRIDAY, THROUGHOUT THE YEAR. CARE IS AVAILABLE TO CHILDREN AGES 8 WEEKS THROUGH TEN YEARS OF AGE. THE PROGRAM: - SUPPORTS WOMEN AND FAMILIES, ALLOWING THEM TO REMAIN ECONOMICALLY SELF-SUFFICIENT, BY PROVIDING STABLE AND AFFORDABLE HIGH QUALITY CHILDCARE FOR CHILDREN THROUGHOUT THE YEAR. - SUPPORTS THE HEALTHY DEVELOPMENT AND ACADEMIC ACHIEVEMENT OF YOUNG CHILDREN BY PROVIDING HIGH QUALITY EARLY EDUCATION AND AFTER SCHOOL PROGRAMS.

Activity2.Description: SEXUAL ASSAULT CRISIS: THE YWCA SEXUAL ASSAULT CRISIS SERVICE ASSISTS THE VICTIMS OF SEXUAL ASSAULT THROUGH CRISIS INTERVENTION AND ADVOCACY, AND WORKS TO PREVENT THE CRIME THROUGH EDUCATION EFFORTS. SERVICES INCLUDED ARE: 24-HOUR HOTLINES; INDIVIDUAL AND GROUP COUNSELING; CRISIS INTERVENTION; ACCOMPANIMENT AND MEDICAL, POLICE, AND COURT ADVOCACY; PREVENTION EDUCATION; INFORMATION AND REFERRALS. THE PROGRAM OPERATES IN A 43 TOWN CONNECTICUT REGION THAT INCLUDES ALL OF HARTFORD COUNTY, PART OF TOLLAND COUNTY, AND PLYMOUTH.SPECIFIC PROGRAM GOALS INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING:LONG TERM:1. REDUCE THE NUMBER OF INSTANCES OF SEXUAL ASSAULT.2. REDUCE THE AFFECTS OF SEXUAL ASSAULT ON INDIVIDUALS WHO HAVE ALREADY BEEN VICTIMIZED.INTERMEDIATE:1. INCREASE THE NUMBER OF SEXUAL ASSAULT VICTIMS SEEKING ASSISTANCE.2. REDUCE THE ON-GOING SYMPTOMS OF TRAUMA SUFFERED BY VICTIMS OF SEXUAL ASSAULT.3. ESTABLISH SERVICES TO VICTIMS OF SEXUAL ASSAULT ON ALL COLLEGE CAMPUSES IN SERVICE REGION.SHORT TERM:RANDOM SAMPLING OF CLIENTS WHO RECEIVE HOTLINE SERVICES WILL STATE THAT AFTER THEIR INITIAL CONTACT ON THE HOTLINE THEY: - FEEL CALMER - ARE ABLE TO IDENTIFY SOME CHOICES FOR THEMSELVES AND MAKE SOME DECISIONS - FEEL SUPPORTED NOW AS COMPARED TO WHEN THEY FIRST CALLED - ARE FEELING BETTERCLIENTS WHO ATTEND A MINIMUM OF 6 COUNSELING SESSIONS WILL STATE THAT AFTER THEIR SESSIONS THEY: - UNDERSTAND THAT THE ASSAULT/ABUSE WAS NOT THEIR FAULT - BLAME THE PERPETRATOR(S) FOR THE ASSAULT/ABUSE AND NOT THEMSELVES - UNDERSTAND THE STAGES OF RECOVERY - FEEL LESS ANXIOUS WHEN THEY THINK ABOUT RECOVERY - CAN IDENTIFY TRIGGERS - CAN EFFECTIVELY COPE AND MANAGE THE INCREASE OR DECREASE OF TRIGGERS - FEEL MORE LIKELY TO TRUST THEIR DECISIONS THAN THEY DID BEFORE COUNSELING - UNDERSTAND THE DYNAMICS OF ABUSE - UNDERSTAND THE DYNAMICS OF TRAUMA - CAN IDENTIFY THEIR GOALS - KNOW WHERE TO TURN TO FOR SUPPORT IF NECESSARYCLIENTS RECEIVING ADVOCACY SERVICES (THROUGH HOSPITAL EXAMINATION PROCESS, LAW ENFORCEMENT EVIDENCE COLLECTION AND INVESTIGATION, AND COURT PROCEDURES) WILL STATE THAT BECAUSE OF THE ADVOCACY THEY RECEIVED, THEY: - FEEL EMOTIONALLY SUPPORTED THROUGH THE PROCESS - FEEL SATISFIED WITH THEIR ROLE IN THE PROCESS - FEEL EMPOWERED TO NAVIGATE THE SYSTEM (MEDICAL, POLICE OR LEGAL/COURT) - ARE ABLE TO DESCRIBE A PLAN FOR NAVIGATING THE SYSTEMCLIENTS WHO ATTEND SUPPORT GROUP(S) WILL STATE THAT DUE TO THE GROUP(S) THEY: - HAVE LEARNED TOOLS TO BETTER EXPRESS FEELINGS - HAVE ALREADY USED THE TOOLS LEARNED IN THE GROUP TO EXPRESS FEELINGS OUTSIDE THE GROUP - FEEL MORE IN CONTROL AND TRUST THEIR DECISIONS MORE THAN BEFORE PARTICIPATING IN THE GROUP - HAVE LEARNED THE TOOLS TO INCREASE THEIR SELF-ESTEEM - ARE PRACTICING MORE EFFECTIVE COPING SKILLS AND CHOOSING HEALTHY BEHAVIORS - HAVE ACHIEVED THEIR PERSONAL GOALS THEY DEVELOPED AT THE BEGINNING OF THE GROUP - FEEL SUPPORTED BY AND CONNECTED TO OTHER MEMBERS OF THE GROUP - SUPPORTED OTHER MEMBERS OF THE GROUP - FELT COMFORTABLE AND SAFE - LEARNED FROM THE EXPERIENCES OF OTHER MEMBERS OF THE GROUP - RECEIVED INFORMATION THAT WAS NEW AND HELPFULINCREASE THE NUMBER OF MIDDLE, HIGH AND COLLEGE AGE STUDENTS WHO CAN: - APPROPRIATELY IDENTIFY BEHAVIOR AS SEXUAL HARASSMENT, PRECURSOR TO SEXUAL ASSAULT. - RESPOND APPROPRIATELY TO SEXUAL ASSAULT OR HARASSMENT. - IDENTIFY MEDIA AND OTHER SOCIETAL MESSAGES THAT GLAMORIZE MALE VIOLENCE OR VIOLENCE AGAINST WOMEN. - AVOID SITUATIONS THAT CAN CONTRIBUTE TO SEXUAL VIOLENCE.

Activity3.Description: DANCE AND FITNESS PROGRAMS: THE YWCA OFFERS A VARIETY OF DANCE AND FITNESS PROGRAMS FOR AGES, CHILDREN-ADULT. FITNESS PROGRAMS INCLUDE A VARIETY OF EXERCISE AND RELAXATION PROGRAMS. INCLUDED ARE CARDIO AND AEROBIC EXERCISE PROGRAMS, YOGA, TAI CHI, AND DANCE FOR BEGINNER THROUGH ADVANCED LEVELS. DANCE CLASSES INCLUDE TAP, JAZZ, BALLET, POINT, HIP-HOP, FUNK, BREAKDANCING AND BALLROOM. CLASSES ARE AVAILABLE 6 DAYS PER WEEK. INDIVIDUAL SESSIONS WITH A PERSONAL TRAINER OR MASSAGE THERAPIST ARE ALSO AVAILABLE.MEDIASMART, A CURRICULUM DEVELOPED BY THE NATIONAL INSTITUTE OF HEALTH AND THE ACADEMY FOR EDUCATION DEVELOPMENT WAS OFFERED TO GIRLS ENROLLED IN THE YWCA STRIVE AFTER SCHOOL PROGRAM FOR MIDDLE SCHOOL STUDENTS. MEDIASMART COMBINES THE ANALYSIS OF MEDIA MESSAGES ABOUT FOOD, INSTRUCTION ON HEALTHY EATING AND IDENTIFYING EATING DISORDERS WITH OPPORTUNITIES FOR HEALTHY EXERCISE.HEALTHY TOMORROWS IS A PARTNERSHIP WITH THE COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER OF NEW BRITAIN. TARGETING HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS WHO MEET REGULARLY WITH A COUNSELOR TO PARTICIPATE IN ACTIVITIES THAT PROMOTE A HEALTHY LIFESTYLE, THE YWCA HAS OPENED ITS FITNESS FACILITIES FOR USE BY THE NEW BRITAIN HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS ENROLLED IN THE PROGRAM.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: VOTING MEMBERS ARE ANY FEMALE MEMBERS OVER THE AGE OF 15.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE NOMINATING COMMITTEE RESEARCHES AND PROPOSES A SLATE OF NOMINEES FOR THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE YWCA OF NEW BRITAIN HOLDS AN ANNUAL MEETING IN JUNE WHERE THE VOTING MEMBERS ELECT THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND THE NOMINATING COMMITTEE.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: ALL FINAL DECISIONS ARE APPROVED BY THE ENTIRE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF THE YWCA OF NEW BRITAIN.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE FINANCE COMMITTEE OF THE YWCA NEW BRITAIN'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS PRESENTED WITH THE FORM 990 FOR THEIR REVIEW. THEY THEN PRESENT THEIR FINDINGS AND OPINIONS TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE FORM 990 IS AVAILABLE TO ANY MEMBER OF THE GOVERNING BODY UPON THEIR REQUEST.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: ALL DIRECTORS COMPLETE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST DECLARATION. ALL REASONABLE ACTION IS TAKEN TO MAKE SURE THERE IS NO REAL OR PERCEIVED CONFLICT OF INTEREST IN AWARDING YWCA BUSINESS TO ANY VENDOR. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS APPROVES ALL MATERIAL CONTRACTS.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE YWCA'S COMPENSATION PAY SCALES WERE ESTABLISHED AND REVIEWED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. PAY SCALES ARE REVIEWED ANNUALLY BY SENIOR MANAGERS FOR ALL STAFF AND ANY ADJUSTMENTS TO PAY SCALES ARE PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR APPROVAL. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS DETERMINES THE COMPENSATION FOR THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE YWCA NEW BRITAIN'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST WITHIN 48 HOURS OF THE REQUEST.
